article.headline: Rhode Island 89, St. Bonaventure 78
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Jimmy Baron and Joe Mbang scored 19 points each to give Rhode Island an 89-78 win over St. Bonaventure on Wednesday night. Darrell Harris added 11 and both Kahiem Seawright and Will Daniels chipped in with 10 points for URI. Rhode Island (11-8, 4-1 Atlantic 10) led by as many as 21 points and held on after St. Bonaventure put together an 11-2 run to pull within 59-45. Paul Williams led St. Bonaventure (4-13, 1-3) with 23 points and Tyler Relph added 20. Michael Lee finished with 16 points. The Rhode Island led 45-34 at halftime and held a double-digit advantage the entire second half. Baron made it a 55-34 lead with a three-pointer at the 17:37 mark as Rhode Island scored the first 10 points of the second half. Williams scored six points in an 11-2 St. Bonaventure run and had a dunk at the 14:05 mark to make it 59-45. Rhode Island answered with a 3-pointer from Will Daniels and a Daniels dunk to give URI a 64-49 lead. St. Bonaventure had scored nine straight to open up a 15-9 first-half lead behind four points from Michael Lee. Rhode Island answered with an 11-0 run to take a 20-9 lead.
